  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Giving ALAS to children born with immunodeficiency</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Out of 100 children born without immune system each year, 70 will die before five years old due to lack of medical diagnostic. Primary Immunodeficiencies led to serious infections in children, like pneumonias, and first contact medical personnel cannot identify the cause. This project will give training to 5000 medical doctors in 8 countries in Latin America to allow them to identify these diseases early in time giving children the opportunity and hope to survive with adequate treatment.</narrative>
  </description>
